00:00:03.469 --> 00:00:07.570
Namaskar! Welcome to Nishmadhulika.com

00:00:08.117 --> 00:00:13.828
Today we will make Date chutney. It is very delicious.

00:00:14.140 --> 00:00:18.562
You can have it with poori's and paranthas or samosa and kachori.

00:00:19.352 --> 00:00:22.209
You can store this chutney for quite long.

00:00:22.656 --> 00:00:25.843
Let's start making Date chutney.

00:00:26.789 --> 00:00:31.554
Dates - 10-12

00:00:31.836 --> 00:00:40.218
These are fresh dates, but if fresh is not available
then you can take dried ones and soak them in water.

00:00:40.578 --> 00:00:45.843
Dates (in grams) - 100-150 grams.

00:00:46.500 --> 00:00:50.046
Sugar - ½ cup.

00:00:50.383 --> 00:00:51.984
Raisins - 2 tbsp.

00:00:52.734 --> 00:00:59.367
Ginger paste - 2 tsp (grated 2 inch piece)

00:01:00.063 --> 00:01:01.492
Asafoetida - 1 pinch.

00:01:01.828 --> 00:01:03.992
Red chilly powder - ½ tsp.

00:01:04.484 --> 00:01:06.593
Mixed spices - ½  tsp.

00:01:07.172 --> 00:01:09.820
Cumin powder - 1 tsp.

00:01:11.516 --> 00:01:13.781
Black rock salt - ¾ tsp.

00:01:14.195 --> 00:01:18.031
Salt - ½ tsp (according to taste)

00:01:18.438 --> 00:01:20.796
Dried mango powder - 2 tsp.

00:01:21.117 --> 00:01:28.656
Firstly, we will chop the dates finely and remove its seeds.

00:01:29.523 --> 00:01:31.468
Let's chop the dates.

00:01:31.835 --> 00:01:37.390
Till we chop the dates, let start making sugar syrup too.

00:01:37.953 --> 00:01:41.812
Put sugar into the pan.

00:01:42.125 --> 00:01:49.304
This is half cup sugar, you can also take jaggery instead.

00:01:50.023 --> 00:01:53.562
In this we have added half cup of water.

00:01:54.976 --> 00:01:55.921
Turn on the stove.

00:01:56.640 --> 00:02:00.101
Let the syrup cook till sugar gets dissolved with the water.

00:02:00.742 --> 00:02:08.617
Remove dates stalk and the seeds.

00:02:11.047 --> 00:02:14.960
Then chop the dates finely into thin pieces.

00:02:43.797 --> 00:02:47.031
We have chopped the dates.

00:02:47.289 --> 00:02:50.648
The sugar has dissolved in the water too.

00:02:51.297 --> 00:02:55.804
Now, add the dates into the syrup.

00:03:01.805 --> 00:03:29.534
Then raisins, ginger paste, mixed spices, red chilly powder,
cumin powder, black rock salt, salt and asafoetida.

00:03:32.401 --> 00:03:42.456
Add dried mango powder and mix everything well, till it turns thick.

00:03:45.956 --> 00:03:49.964
The chutney has turned all nice and thick.

00:03:50.300 --> 00:03:53.497
It took around 6-7 minutes to make the chutney.

00:03:53.800 --> 00:03:59.432
We made the syrup added everything else.

00:03:59.838 --> 00:04:06.526
And the chutney was all prepared within 6-7 minutes.
Take it out in a bowl. Turn off the gas.

00:04:10.463 --> 00:04:15.729
A very nice and delicious date chutney is ready.

00:04:16.019 --> 00:04:20.909
You can serve it with poori and paranthas.

00:04:21.503 --> 00:04:27.417
Give it to the children in their tiffin boxes, they will love it a lot.

00:04:27.885 --> 00:04:32.870
You can store in the fridge and consume till 2 months.

00:04:33.636 --> 00:04:40.432
You can make your Date chutney, eat it and enjoy it.
And share you experiences with us at Nishamundlika.com

00:04:40.902 --> 00:04:46.888
We shall meet again with a new recipe.
